In his article ' Blind Reasoning ' , Boghossian argues that we are blind to our reasons for justifying our methods of inference ( the epitome of a method of inference is taken to be modus ponens . ) Rejecting both Simple Inferential Externalism for its inconsistency and Simple Inferential Internalism because it is difficult to accept , he opts for a third and new form of " rational insight " .
